WEBVTT

00:01.960 --> 00:04.546
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

00:36.370 --> 00:38.580
( both laughing )

00:42.209 --> 00:43.961
It's bigger
than I thought.

00:44.044 --> 00:45.379
( both laugh )

00:52.886 --> 00:56.640
Jimmy:
<i>This is nice. This is nice.
This is fuckin' nice.</i>

00:58.475 --> 01:00.435
This is nice.

01:00.519 --> 01:01.812
( shaking spray paint can )

01:03.522 --> 01:04.940
<i>Oh, man.</i>

01:08.694 --> 01:10.320
‐ <i>G‐Bo.</i>
‐ Yeah?

01:12.155 --> 01:14.116
‐ ( laughs )
‐ How ya doin', Pop?

01:15.367 --> 01:17.619
<i>Oh, man.</i>

01:17.703 --> 01:19.329
<i>Now we're in room 104.</i>

01:20.455 --> 01:22.833
‐ What a trip.
‐ Great set.

01:22.916 --> 01:24.626
What a trip.

01:24.710 --> 01:27.462
<i>( rock music playing )</i>

01:32.593 --> 01:36.430
Oh, look at this.
This is good stuff here too.
Look at this, G‐Bo.

01:36.513 --> 01:39.558
Oh, my God. They got
all kinds of stuff over here.

01:39.641 --> 01:41.977
There's a lot of dynamics
with this room.

01:46.982 --> 01:49.860
Oh, G‐Bo! Look at this.
Look at this.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.236
( pats box spring )

01:51.320 --> 01:53.405
‐ Yeah, that's good.
‐ Perfect.

01:53.488 --> 01:55.407
It's got like
a canvas texture to it.

01:55.490 --> 01:56.783
Perfect.

01:56.867 --> 01:58.910
Jimmy:
<i>If you had told me
a year ago,</i>

01:58.994 --> 02:00.787
where we were
and where we are,

02:00.871 --> 02:04.249
that this is the deal,
I would've never believed it.

02:04.333 --> 02:06.543
‐ <i>OK, so I have a thought.</i>
‐ What?

02:06.627 --> 02:08.670
I think if we flip
these babies around

02:08.754 --> 02:11.423
and throw‐‐
get our paint on 'em,
they're gonna dry,

02:11.506 --> 02:13.508
and then we can
flip 'em back around

02:13.592 --> 02:16.386
and put our‐‐ our strings on
while they're kinda drying.

02:16.470 --> 02:18.930
'Cause at some point
I'm gonna put it on the wall.

02:19.014 --> 02:19.973
OK.

02:21.308 --> 02:23.852
These are nice and light,
this is perfect.

02:23.935 --> 02:26.605
<i>‐ The box springs are light.
‐ They're like a canvas,</i>

02:26.688 --> 02:29.358
<i>so the objective
is to use the box springs</i>

02:29.441 --> 02:31.735
so we have
two separate pieces‐‐

02:31.818 --> 02:33.987
Gianni Arone,
Jimmy Ray Flynn‐‐

02:34.071 --> 02:36.657
and then everything else
is up for grabs.

02:40.535 --> 02:41.828
Yeah, nice.

02:41.912 --> 02:44.289
<i>Uh, you're not
gonna hit the edges?</i>

02:44.373 --> 02:45.874
I'm just going...

02:45.957 --> 02:48.752
‐ Hit those edges.
‐ You hit those edges.

02:48.835 --> 02:51.546
‐ OK.
‐ I didn't mean it for real.

02:51.630 --> 02:53.548
( laughs )

02:55.217 --> 02:56.093
‐ Hey.
‐ What?

02:56.176 --> 02:57.594
You said I could hit the edges.

02:57.677 --> 02:59.805
‐ No, leave it.
‐ No, baby, come on.

02:59.888 --> 03:02.099
‐ They gotta have the balance.
‐ <i>No, they don't.</i>

03:02.182 --> 03:04.643
‐ No, you don't.
‐ Just let me finish it.

03:04.726 --> 03:06.186
All right.

03:11.983 --> 03:13.693
Yeah, I'm gonna have to wait
till this dries.

03:13.777 --> 03:15.445
Yeah, it's gotta
dry a little bit.

03:15.529 --> 03:17.531
Do you wanna do like...

03:17.614 --> 03:19.157
a lamp, or you want
to do something else?

03:19.241 --> 03:21.576
Because I'm gonna be doing
some collage stuff.

03:27.999 --> 03:29.668
Gianni:
<i>I'm not an artist</i>

03:29.751 --> 03:31.336
who is formally trained

03:31.420 --> 03:33.922
<i>and who is doing oils</i>

03:34.005 --> 03:36.675
<i>and, like, rendering
lifelike drawings.</i>

03:36.758 --> 03:39.177
<i>I just like makin'.</i>

03:39.261 --> 03:41.555
Jimmy:
<i>Looks good.</i>

03:41.638 --> 03:45.350
Did I spell "experiencing"
right? Dad?

03:45.434 --> 03:47.686
Oh, shit. Is this, like,
a spelling thing?

03:47.769 --> 03:49.813
‐ I don't know.
‐ "Experien..."

03:49.896 --> 03:51.523
<i>Can't tell.
I can't remember.</i>

03:51.606 --> 03:53.734
Spelling's not my thing.

03:53.817 --> 03:58.321
I think so.
Jimi Hendrix Experience.
Let's see...

03:58.405 --> 04:00.615
‐ I don't know.
‐ Yeah, it's fine.

04:00.699 --> 04:03.034
Jimmy:
<i>I work fast
and in the moment,</i>

04:03.118 --> 04:05.162
<i>I stay in the process.</i>

04:05.245 --> 04:07.080
<i>( Jimmy laughing )</i>

04:07.164 --> 04:09.666
<i>I like that. I like
when you do that shit.</i>

04:09.750 --> 04:10.959
That's, like, my favorite,

04:11.042 --> 04:12.878
when you start
spoofing on heads.

04:12.961 --> 04:15.589
Gianni:
<i>I just like getting into it,</i>

04:15.672 --> 04:17.716
<i>and I love installations.</i>

04:17.799 --> 04:21.052
So to be able to use
the parameters of the room...

04:21.136 --> 04:23.472
<i>because it's an installation.</i>

04:24.931 --> 04:28.393
I like that. That's great.
We gotta chop that wall up.

04:28.477 --> 04:30.228
<i>That's a piece.</i>

04:30.312 --> 04:32.939
<i>Jimmy:
I am his biggest fan.
I'm his number‐‐</i>

04:33.023 --> 04:35.358
I love a lot of artists,
but he's‐‐ he's the best.

04:35.442 --> 04:38.570
Gianni, you picked out
some really good things.

04:38.653 --> 04:40.697
This is great.
It's got tape on it, too.

04:40.781 --> 04:41.907
Yeah, that's
the one I liked.

04:41.990 --> 04:43.950
‐ You keep this one.
‐ No, use it.

04:44.034 --> 04:45.202
‐ Keep it.
‐ Use it.

04:45.285 --> 04:46.620
OK.

04:46.703 --> 04:48.330
Jimmy:
<i>He kinda like inspired me.</i>

04:48.413 --> 04:51.917
<i>We had talked
about collaborating
for a long time,</i>

04:52.000 --> 04:54.169
<i>but there's something
that happened this year</i>

04:54.252 --> 04:57.214
<i>with Gianni dealing with his‐‐</i>

04:57.297 --> 04:58.590
I call it "mental wellness,"

04:58.673 --> 05:00.967
that allowed it to flow

05:01.051 --> 05:02.385
in a way that
didn't feel forced.

05:02.469 --> 05:04.554
<i>I said, "Hey, man,
you wanna do this?"</i>

05:04.638 --> 05:07.682
<i>"Yeah, let's do it."
We started doing it.</i>

05:09.226 --> 05:11.144
I like this, G‐Bo.

05:11.228 --> 05:13.480
I like the two ones.

05:13.563 --> 05:15.482
‐ Yeah?
‐ Yeah.

05:15.565 --> 05:16.858
I like it.

05:16.942 --> 05:20.070
This is like
my favorite material.
Yeah.

05:27.536 --> 05:30.372
Jimmy:
<i>Can you get out of that light
for a second, please?</i>

05:31.540 --> 05:34.125
‐ Yeah, you.
‐ ( camera clicks )

05:34.209 --> 05:36.795
Tell me that
doesn't look fucking cool.

05:36.878 --> 05:38.588
Yeah.

05:38.672 --> 05:40.507
Gianni:
<i>I know a lot of my friends</i>

05:40.590 --> 05:42.884
<i>have fractured relationships
with their dads.</i>

05:49.558 --> 05:51.226
Younger Jimmy:
<i>My buddies.</i>

05:53.812 --> 05:55.772
Say, "Hi, Mom."

05:55.856 --> 05:59.359
Gianni:
<i>As a little kid, I just
remember a present father.</i>

06:03.238 --> 06:05.282
<i>He just created, like,</i>

06:05.365 --> 06:07.826
<i>a nurturing environment
for creativity.</i>

06:07.909 --> 06:10.829
<i>He would put on,
like, Tracy Chapman and music</i>

06:10.912 --> 06:13.873
<i>and we would get pots and pans
and play the drums.</i>

06:13.957 --> 06:16.167
Jimmy:
<i>Happy birthday.
I'm gonna go now.</i>

06:16.251 --> 06:18.169
I want you to give me a kiss.

06:18.253 --> 06:19.671
( kiss )

06:19.754 --> 06:23.633
<i>And he's grown into
my best friend.</i>

06:23.717 --> 06:25.927
<i>It wasn't always like that.</i>

06:28.263 --> 06:30.682
Jimmy:
<i>Ahh, yeah,</i>

06:30.765 --> 06:33.268
it really didn't start to happen
until the friggin'‐‐

06:33.351 --> 06:35.478
started with
the drugs and alcohol.

06:35.562 --> 06:37.856
I mean, that's when it just
became a whole 'nother animal.

06:37.939 --> 06:43.028
That's when it started to be
this clear kind of... uh‐oh.

06:43.111 --> 06:44.362
( paint can rattling )

06:44.446 --> 06:46.364
You gotta be careful
with the spray paint, though.

06:46.448 --> 06:48.450
‐ I know.
‐ All right.

06:51.244 --> 06:53.705
Gianni:
<i>Yeah, it was
shortly after high school</i>

06:53.788 --> 06:56.875
<i>when I just opened up
to something and I just</i>

06:56.958 --> 06:58.877
( snaps fingers )
went in. I mean,

06:58.960 --> 07:02.255
you go from smokin' weed
after high school

07:02.339 --> 07:03.590
to next year doin' meth,

07:03.673 --> 07:06.176
‐ like smokin' crystal meth,
‐ Ohh.

07:06.259 --> 07:07.886
‐ which is just like a‐‐
‐ The fuckin' worst.

07:07.969 --> 07:10.096
<i>Which is like a epidemic
of a drug,</i>

07:10.180 --> 07:13.975
<i>and took me to places
I thought I'd never go to</i>

07:14.059 --> 07:16.770
emotionally, physically,

07:16.853 --> 07:19.189
mentally, spiritually,
psychologically.

07:19.272 --> 07:20.982
It'll steal your friggin' soul.
I don't give a shit,

07:21.066 --> 07:22.651
I hear him say the word "meth,"

07:22.734 --> 07:25.570
and I get like, "I'm goin'
to another place now,"

07:25.654 --> 07:28.114
'cause I just‐‐
it's, like, <i>evil.</i>

07:29.824 --> 07:32.452
Gianni:
<i>Not only did I do meth,
but I did LSD,</i>

07:32.535 --> 07:33.703
<i>I did mushrooms,
I smoked weed.</i>

07:33.787 --> 07:35.622
<i>I smoked heroin once.</i>

07:35.705 --> 07:36.998
<i>I went down
the pipeline of,</i>

07:37.082 --> 07:39.292
"What does it do?
How does it affect me?

07:39.376 --> 07:40.377
Let's try it."

07:42.504 --> 07:45.423
<i>I was microdosing LSD for,
like, a year straight.</i>

07:45.507 --> 07:50.178
<i>And, like, that has a huge
effect on your brain chemistry,</i>

07:50.261 --> 07:53.014
and I started hearing voices.

08:00.355 --> 08:03.984
I'm gonna start my collaging.
I'm gonna collage over here.

08:04.067 --> 08:06.069
I'm gonna work over here.

08:06.152 --> 08:08.279
<i>You know, it's interesting
we're doing this now,</i>

08:08.363 --> 08:11.199
we're literally coming up
on the year anniversary.

08:13.702 --> 08:16.121
Let me just back it up
a second.

08:16.204 --> 08:18.123
Younger Jimmy:
<i>Make a little wish, OK?</i>

08:18.206 --> 08:20.625
<i>The night Gianni was born,
I remember him coming out</i>

08:20.709 --> 08:23.128
<i>and watching the life
come into his body.</i>

08:23.211 --> 08:25.213
<i>He just looked at me.
It was surreal.</i>

08:26.297 --> 08:30.802
Cut to December fifth...

08:30.885 --> 08:32.887
of last year.

08:32.971 --> 08:35.849
He came to my house

08:35.932 --> 08:38.810
in a full‐blown
psychotic episode.

08:38.893 --> 08:40.770
I didn't know
who the fuck he was.

08:45.817 --> 08:47.777
<i>We had this thing
literally in the backyard,</i>

08:47.861 --> 08:50.113
<i>we were sitting there,
we were talking
across from each other,</i>

08:50.196 --> 08:51.990
<i>and he was like
in a full‐blown episode.</i>

08:52.073 --> 08:53.408
<i>At one point he said to me,</i>

08:53.491 --> 08:55.535
"Don't worry,
I'm not gonna kill you."

08:55.618 --> 08:57.996
And I thought,
"Is this motherfucker
thinkin' about killin' me?"

08:58.079 --> 09:00.290
<i>And I was petrified.</i>

09:00.373 --> 09:02.542
<i>I said, "Gianni,
I'm gonna go in the house
and get some water."</i>

09:02.625 --> 09:04.294
I went in the house
and I called the cops.

09:04.377 --> 09:06.921
And I said, "You gotta come
and get my son."

09:09.132 --> 09:10.258
<i>Ahh...</i>

09:10.341 --> 09:12.927
All I know is, it was like

09:13.011 --> 09:15.930
the hardest thing
I've ever had to do in my life.

09:21.269 --> 09:24.522
<i>The cops come,
Gianni got in the car</i>

09:24.606 --> 09:26.357
<i>and, you know,
they took him</i>

09:26.441 --> 09:28.026
to the fucking psych unit
and shit,

09:28.109 --> 09:30.028
and we went there,
first night I go in,

09:30.111 --> 09:32.697
<i>he's like fuckin'
doing cartwheels</i>

09:32.781 --> 09:34.032
<i>or backflips in the thing,</i>

09:34.115 --> 09:35.533
<i>he's head‐butting me,</i>

09:35.617 --> 09:37.494
<i>he's really angry,
really agitated.</i>

09:37.577 --> 09:38.995
<i>And then we found out</i>

09:39.079 --> 09:41.623
<i>that he's got
a dual diagnosis.</i>

09:41.706 --> 09:45.293
Couple that with the addiction‐‐
it's a mental illness.

09:45.376 --> 09:48.296
So now you're dealing with
a whole 'nother thing.

09:50.548 --> 09:53.968
‐ How ya doin', G?
‐ Eh.

09:54.052 --> 09:56.221
Yeah, it's...

09:56.304 --> 09:59.390
‐ It's all over the place.
‐ Yeah.

09:59.474 --> 10:01.851
All right, well,
it's your thing, baby.

10:09.943 --> 10:11.653
Let's put a whole series
together...

10:11.736 --> 10:14.489
Gianni:
<i>I've been diagnosed
bipolar I and II,</i>

10:14.572 --> 10:16.699
<i>schizoaffective,
schizophrenic.</i>

10:16.783 --> 10:19.702
<i>I don't know
if my mental illness was
caused from my drug use‐‐</i>

10:19.786 --> 10:21.913
Is it chemically induced
mental illness,

10:21.996 --> 10:23.832
or is actually something
that's biological?

10:23.915 --> 10:25.333
Or something
that onset later?

10:27.001 --> 10:28.920
<i>They would diagnose me,</i>

10:29.003 --> 10:30.922
<i>and I'd do the meds
for a little bit,</i>

10:31.005 --> 10:33.174
<i>then I'd take myself off 'em
because I was just like,</i>

10:33.258 --> 10:35.802
<i>I'm an alcoholic
and I'm an addict,</i>

10:35.885 --> 10:37.262
<i>and I like feeling high,</i>

10:37.345 --> 10:40.598
and when I'm unmedicated
and I go into mania,

10:40.682 --> 10:42.392
<i>I feel high from that.</i>

10:45.395 --> 10:46.980
I like feeling a little off,

10:47.063 --> 10:48.565
I like feeling
a little weird,

10:48.648 --> 10:50.942
I like feeling a little askew

10:51.025 --> 10:54.195
<i>and not totally
bolted to the ground.</i>

10:57.240 --> 10:59.117
Can you throw me
one of those rags real quick?

10:59.200 --> 11:00.368
<i>Like the big hand?</i>

11:02.078 --> 11:04.622
It's a little too big
for my taste, but‐‐

11:04.706 --> 11:06.374
Can you throw me
one of those rags, please?

11:08.459 --> 11:10.587
Maybe it is
too big of a hand.

11:12.755 --> 11:15.717
Wanna have a seat?
Wanna sit down?

11:15.800 --> 11:17.552
G‐Bo.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.262
Wanna sit down?

11:23.183 --> 11:26.477
I don't like it at all
right now.

11:26.561 --> 11:29.314
There's no question
in my mind
you're gonna get there.

11:29.397 --> 11:31.524
No, I know, I'm not
worried about getting there.

11:31.608 --> 11:35.570
You jumped in,
the paint was still wet...

11:35.653 --> 11:38.031
‐ You know what I mean?
‐ Looks like a big chicken.

11:38.114 --> 11:39.908
<i>I don't see a chicken
at all.</i>

11:39.991 --> 11:41.993
<i>I just see like
a fuckin'...</i>

11:42.076 --> 11:44.495
‐ A blob.
‐ I don't see a blob,

11:44.579 --> 11:47.916
I just see a very exaggerated,
grotesque...

11:47.999 --> 11:50.585
If I were you,
one of the things I would do is,

11:50.668 --> 11:54.839
I would hit your canvas
so there's kind of
a little bit more white to it,

11:54.923 --> 11:58.301
and then as you go over it,
the other things will pop out.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.011
‐ Yeah, I agree.
‐ Right?

12:00.094 --> 12:01.471
So just hit it again.

12:05.183 --> 12:06.976
What are you doin'?
Why don't you hit it
with the roller?

12:07.060 --> 12:08.603
<i>'Cause I don't like
the roller.</i>

12:08.686 --> 12:12.899
Ohh, Gianni,
the paint's gonna
take forever to dry.

12:13.942 --> 12:15.693
Ohh.

12:15.777 --> 12:18.905
He's not fuckin' listenin'
to me.

12:21.115 --> 12:22.825
<i>The way you're doing that,
man, it's gonna take</i>

12:22.909 --> 12:24.786
a long time to dry.

12:27.580 --> 12:30.124
These are lessons
that I was supposed to learn

12:30.208 --> 12:32.543
about, like, backin' off,

12:32.627 --> 12:34.921
not micromanaging.

12:36.965 --> 12:38.258
<i>Yeah, man,
I would just hit that.</i>

12:38.341 --> 12:39.842
<i>Hit the edge too.</i>

12:40.969 --> 12:42.303
<i>Yeah, there you go,
brother.</i>

12:44.097 --> 12:45.807
Yeah, man, that's much better.

12:49.018 --> 12:52.146
Gianni:
<i>For me, being born
into a human body</i>

12:52.230 --> 12:55.233
on planet Earth
didn't make sense to me.

12:55.316 --> 12:57.568
<i>I'm like, what am I‐‐
what is this?</i>

12:57.652 --> 13:00.863
<i>What's this night/day,
love/hate, good/bad,</i>

13:00.947 --> 13:03.449
<i>all this polarity,
all this separation?</i>

13:03.533 --> 13:06.661
<i>This doesn't make sense
to my inherent nature
and my inherent being</i>

13:06.744 --> 13:10.540
<i>of oneness and completeness
and, like, a unified whole.</i>

13:10.623 --> 13:13.584
<i>I feel fractured and separated
and alone and weird,</i>

13:13.668 --> 13:17.755
and I've always been fascinated
with the moment of death,

13:17.839 --> 13:21.467
<i>and so I...</i>

13:21.551 --> 13:24.095
wanted to meet death
a couple times on my own sword.

13:24.178 --> 13:26.889
Maybe I'll just do
a big horse on it.

13:32.228 --> 13:34.355
<i>For me, I had...</i>

13:34.439 --> 13:37.025
<i>two attempts on my life,</i>

13:37.108 --> 13:39.944
<i>one was when I was younger,</i>

13:40.028 --> 13:42.780
<i>and then the last one
was more intentional.</i>

13:42.864 --> 13:44.657
Gonna wait
for it to dry.

13:44.741 --> 13:47.452
I had an episode
that I can only describe

13:47.535 --> 13:49.454
as losing the letters
and the numbers.

13:49.537 --> 13:52.415
<i>I couldn't articulate myself,
and therefore,</i>

13:52.498 --> 13:54.459
<i>when I came out
of the psychosis</i>

13:54.542 --> 13:55.793
<i>I couldn't relate to anyone.</i>

13:55.877 --> 13:58.588
<i>And I created this rig,</i>

13:58.671 --> 14:01.632
<i>and I was about
to turn on the switch,</i>

14:01.716 --> 14:03.384
and then there was
a knock on my door,

14:03.468 --> 14:07.013
and my ex‐girlfriend Sunshine
knocked on‐‐ opened the door

14:07.096 --> 14:10.475
and saved my life,
called my dad.

14:10.558 --> 14:12.518
Jimmy:
<i>As he's telling you
he's whatever,</i>

14:12.602 --> 14:14.395
I have to respect
what he's saying,

14:14.479 --> 14:15.813
'cause it's real for him.

14:15.897 --> 14:18.941
There was a point
when he was either

14:19.025 --> 14:21.069
in the hospital
or just getting out,

14:21.152 --> 14:23.613
I said, "You know something?
I will talk to you,

14:23.696 --> 14:25.239
but I won't talk
to your psychosis."

14:25.323 --> 14:28.743
<i>So for him
to tell you this story,</i>

